    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single deficient factor (Test conditions, achieved Gradation 2 vs. required Gradation 3) is judged acceptable because the single-condition ASTM F1717 protocol is the regulatory standard and the conservative loading scenario bounds clinical use. All three QoIs satisfy quantitative acceptance criteria (E/uval < 1.96; percent difference < 10%). The FEA modeling framework is accepted as credible for the stated COU.",
